## Key facts / hazards
- Canonicalization = Python json.dumps(sort_keys=True) DEFAULTS: ', '/': '
  separators WITH spaces, ensure_ascii=True (\\uXXXX), Python float repr. A TS
  SDK MUST NOT use JSON.stringify. canonical_json is pinned per object/row row.
- bytes_digest = sha256 -> urlsafe_b64 -> replace -=>X, _=>Y, rstrip '='.
  table_digest uses HEX of concatenated row-digest strings (different encoding).
- Validator exception classes are contract: require_* -> CHValidationError,
  validate_tag/alias -> ValueError.
- whole-number/large floats are python_only:true (JSON loses int/float in JS);
  scalar object rows are library-only (a bare scalar is not a server record).
- The server delegates ALL digesting to weave.shared.digest
  (sqlite/clickhouse obj_create:1897/1917 -> compute_object_digest_result(
  req.obj.val, req.obj.builtin_object_class)), so there is one implementation;
  the server test guards against a future change that normalizes around it.

