## Reorg mechanics (for future agents)
- gt fold (from the server branch) merged it into the corpus branch but kept TWO
  commits; squashed via `git reset --soft <parent> && git commit` then
  `gt restack` (clean, no children to fix). This rewrote the SHA, orphaning the
  two prior per-commit notes (1e152ae667 corpus, c47b9e8a29 server) -- their
  content is consolidated here. Did this rather than amend-in-place precisely
  because rewriting orphans notes (conductor+gt memory).

## Freeze discipline
Never edit an existing row's expected (wire-break). Add a new id; keep the old
(mirrors tests/trace/data_serialization). New inputs are always fine: extend the
case lists in generate_fixtures.py and rerun.

